# Ending: Available to Everyone Who Can Find It

You keep the game available. The studio survives launch week. Free-expression defenders praise the platform for not panicking.

By morning, screenshots of the storefront trend again. Critics focus less on the game itself and more on the platform’s recommendation system, autoplay trailer, and weak age warning.

You defended the creator from overreach, but the platform still profited from attention while pretending distribution is passive.

[[View final report->Final Report]]


