# The Moderation Queue

<div class="report">
<strong>CASE ID:</strong> MQ-8841<br>
<strong>Title:</strong> <em>Velvet Mirage: After School Arcana</em><br>
<strong>Flag reason:</strong> sexualized young-looking characters, unclear age rating, advertiser concern, viral user reports.<br>
<strong>Review window:</strong> one shift.
</div>

You are Mara, a trust-and-safety reviewer for a major online game storefront. The game in front of you is not illegal. It is not simple. It is profitable, controversial, stylized, and spreading fast.

Your job is not to discover the obvious answer. Your job is to make a decision the company can defend.

<div class="warning">
<strong>ALERT:</strong> High priority. Press inquiry expected. Resolve before end of shift.
</div>

[[Begin review->Shift Begins]]


:: Storefront {"position":"1150,25","size":"100,100"}
(set: $safety to $safety + 8)
(set: $trust to $trust - 2)
(set: $deadline to $deadline - 1)
(display: "Dashboard")

The storefront page shows cropped promotional images, a fantasy school setting, and tags that include “visual novel,” “romance,” and “mature themes.”

The age warning exists, but it is below the trailer. The trailer autoplay preview appears before the warning.

That design choice matters. The platform is not just hosting the game. It is arranging attention.

[[Require storefront changes->Correction Path]]

[[Check rating information->Rating Check]]

[[Continue to advertiser escalation->Advertiser Escalation]]


:: Trust Automation {"position":"650,25","size":"100,100"}
(set: $safety to $safety + 10)
(set: $consistency to $consistency + 5)
(set: $fairness to $fairness - 10)
(set: $automationReliance to $automationReliance + 2)
(display: "Dashboard")

You mark the machine score as a central reason for action. The dashboard becomes easier to navigate. Several risky screenshots are already highlighted. The path to restriction is clean.

Too clean.

A warning appears: “Creator response deprioritized due to high-risk classification.”

[[Continue to advertiser escalation->Advertiser Escalation]]

[[Force open the creator response anyway->Developer Response]]


:: Use Automation Carefully {"position":"775,25","size":"100,100"}
(set: $safety to $safety + 5)
(set: $fairness to $fairness + 6)
(set: $consistency to $consistency + 4)
(set: $fatigue to $fatigue + 8)
(set: $deadline to $deadline - 1)
(display: "Dashboard")

You keep the score visible, but you refuse to let it become the entire decision. That takes longer. The queue does not reward patience.

<div class="warning">
New cases added to queue: 43.
</div>

[[Open the developer response->Developer Response]]

[[Review user reports->User Reports]]

[[Check advertiser escalation->Advertiser Escalation]]


:: User Reports {"position":"1025,25","size":"100,100"}
(set: $harmSignal to true)
(set: $safety to $safety + 12)
(set: $trust to $trust + 5)
(set: $fatigue to $fatigue + 10)
(set: $deadline to $deadline - 1)
(display: "Dashboard")

<div class="report">
<strong>Report sample:</strong><br>
“My younger sibling saw this on the front page.”<br>
“This is obviously adult content hiding behind cute art.”<br>
“Stop pretending anime style means harmless.”<br>
“This is censorship. Adults can choose what to buy.”
</div>

The reports do not agree on what harm means. Some focus on minors. Some on disgust. Some on exploitation. Some on artistic freedom.

A moderation job turns public conflict into checkboxes.

[[Check age rating information->Rating Check]]

[[Check advertiser escalation->Advertiser Escalation]]

[[Return to policy->Policy Panel]]


